# Case 04 — Insider Data Exfiltration via Android Device: Mobile Forensics Investigation

**Case ID:** DFIR-2024-004  
**Classification:** High — Insider Threat  
**Investigator:** Himanshu Chourasia  
**Tools:** Cellebrite UFED 4PC, MSAB XRY, Magnet AXIOM  
**Duration:** 14 hours (device acquisition → full analysis → legal reporting)

---

## Executive Summary

A pharmaceutical company's HR department raised a concern about a Senior R&D Engineer (`P. Verma`) who had submitted resignation with a 30-day notice and was suspected of exfiltrating proprietary drug formulation data. A forensic examination of the employee's company-issued Android device (Samsung Galaxy S23) and personal device (voluntarily surrendered) revealed a systematic pattern of data exfiltration spanning 6 weeks — including transfer of 14.3 GB of confidential research data to a personal Google Drive account and encrypted messaging with a competitor's recruiter.

All forensic procedures were conducted under a court-issued preservation order. Full chain of custody was maintained.

